  <h2 id="Fun Facts" style="border:4px solid Navy;">Fun Facts</h2>
<p>London is located by Birmingham, and it is on the edge of the country; United Kingdom. A few countries located by London are: Germany and France, which are across from London, a sea is separating them. So if you are looking to travel to London, these are a few areas you can visit too!
Secondly, London is a very diverse city. As one of the most diverse cities in the world, London houses over 8 million residents, who collectively speak over 300 languages, including Bengali, Gujarati, Punjabi, Cantonese, Mandarin, Hokkien and of course English. Thirdly, the Queen lives in the Buckingham Palace, and although she has many other royal residences, the Queen still sometimes resides in Buckingham Palace.</p>
  
  <h2 id="Conclusion" style="border:4px solid Gray;">Conclusion</h2>
<p>Here are a few fun facts about London if you are interested! The Romans founded London at about 50 AD. Its name is derived from the Celtic word Londinios, which means the place of the old one. Some other fascinating and unique things to see in London are the red buses, small black taxi cabs, and the famous red telephone boxes. As you can see, this buzzing city is full of great adventures that were not mentioned above: The British Museum, Madame Tussaud's, Sherlock Holmes Museum, Oxford Street, and of course, Harry Potter World. However, London is mostly known for its stylish malls, its football, and the difference from Canada. </p>

